@xBenJamminx Timing things üò¨

Eventually there will come a time where we as consumers aren‚Äôt competing directly for NFTs, but brands are competing for our attention and will compensate us through some use of fungible and non-fungible tokens

8/8

As more BRANDS try to capture your attention, they won‚Äôt be rewarding you with ‚Äúfake internet money.‚Äù They‚Äôll be rewarding you with collectibles that align with their brand, style, and vision

7 /üßµ

As more creatives enter the space to build out new platforms in this space, they will need to convince you to move your attention from what you‚Äôre already doing to what they‚Äôre building. We see this today with tokens and new marketplaces

6 /üßµ

How do these organizations get more digital participation? Incentivize people to watch their events on TV

The NBA All-Star weekend is soon and @nbatopshot is rewarding people an opportunity to receive an NFT by tuning into select events

5 /üßµ https://t.co/Wu6W9Q2Ps8

All-Star weekend is known to be fairly meh across all sports. The Pro Bowl is worse than two-hand touch, the NBA All-Stars somehow play even less defense than they usually do, I personally only watch the home run derby when MLB All-Star rolls around

4 /üßµ

When we move from the physical to the digital world, we need to move from physical collectibles to digital collectibles (NFTs)

The digital version of rewarding the first 10k fans in the stadium would be rewarding fans who watch the pre-game show or less exciting games

3 /üßµ

The sports entertainment industry has leveraged collectibles for decades to incentivize behavior they want

Baseball teams will giveaway limited, unique items to the first X people in attendance to a home game to incentivize people to spend more time at their stadium

2 /üßµ https://t.co/AH1OgcgDpX

In a digital world where there are an infinite number of things competing for our attention, creators will look to leverage existing human psychology to incentivize desirable interactions on their platforms

Let‚Äôs look at an example that has existed for many decades
